1.	Precondition – The game is running
Action – The user clicks the space bar
Postcondition – A missile is launched

2.	Precondition – There are 5 ships on the screen
Action – A missile hits a ship
Postcondition – The ship hit disappears

3.	Precondition – A missile is fired
Action – The ship is hit
Postcondition – A explosion appears

a)	Precondition – A missile is fired 
Action – The missile misses
Postcondition – The missile exits the screen

4.	Precondition – There are no ships
Action – The solution makes ships
Postcondition – Ships appear moving right to left or left to right 

5.	Precondition – The game is running
Action – 10 ships are hit
Postcondition – the game ends

6.	Precondition – The game started 
Action – The user has not touched any keys
Postcondition – The game ends

7.	Precondition - The game has started
Action – The user clicks the left mouse button
Postcondition – The game ends

8.	Precondition – The ship enters the screen
Action – The ship leaves the screen
Postcondition – The solution removes the ship from being active

While doing this exercise it is nice to see what can go wrong just as much can go right. 
In the ideal game the user would hit a ship every time, however that won’t always be the case.
It made me think of the different possibilities instead of just what is expected to happen. 
